<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="259" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,942,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="259">
Note: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Issiki &amp; Stringer" authorityYear="1932" box="[224,402,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Palaeosetidae" genus="Genustes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutata">
<emphasis box="[224,402,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="259">Genustes lutata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName box="[685,809,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Palaeosetidae" genus="Genustes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutes">
<emphasis box="[685,809,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="259">G. minutes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Issiki, S. T. &amp; Stringer, H." box="[858,1153,1123,1150]" pageId="8" pageNumber="259" pagination="73 - 80" refId="ref9763" refString="Issiki, S. T. &amp; Stringer, H. (1932 b) On new Oriental genera and species of the Hepialoidea (Lepidoptera: Homoneura), Part II. Stylops, 73 - 80. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1932. tb 01355. x" type="book chapter" year="1932">Issiki &amp; Stringer (1932b)</bibRefCitation>
, however, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nielsen, E. S. &amp; Robinson, G. S. &amp; Wagner, D. L." box="[1281,1436,1123,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="259" pagination="823 - 878" refId="ref11031" refString="Nielsen, E. S., Robinson, G. S. &amp; Wagner, D. L. (2000) Ghost - moths of the world: a global inventory and bibliography of the Exoporia (Mnesarchaeoidea and Hepialoidea) (Lepidoptera). Journal of Natural History, 34, 823 - 878. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 002229300299282" type="journal article" year="2000">
Nielsen 
<emphasis box="[1377,1429,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="259">et al</emphasis>
.
</bibRefCitation>
(2000) probably overlooked the latter publication (
<bibRefCitation author="Issiki, S. T. &amp; Stringer, H." box="[762,1027,1159,1186]" pageId="8" pageNumber="259" pagination="73 - 80" refId="ref9763" refString="Issiki, S. T. &amp; Stringer, H. (1932 b) On new Oriental genera and species of the Hepialoidea (Lepidoptera: Homoneura), Part II. Stylops, 73 - 80. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1932. tb 01355. x" type="book chapter" year="1932">Issiki &amp; Stringer 1932b</bibRefCitation>
) and included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Issiki &amp; Stringer" authorityYear="1932" box="[1192,1290,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Palaeosetidae" genus="Genustes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutata">
<emphasis box="[1192,1290,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="259">G. lutata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid species from 
<collectingCountry box="[310,371,1195,1221]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="259">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
